<p>
Let \(T:V\to W\) be a linear map.
</p>
<p>
The <b>dual map</b> of \(T\) is the linear map
\[T^*:W^*\to V^*\]
such that \(T^*\alpha = \alpha T\) for all \(\alpha\in W^*\).
Here, \(W^*\) and \(V^*\)
denote the <a knowl="defs/vec/dual">dual spaces</a> of
\(W\) and \(V\) respectively.
</p>
</body>
</html>
